  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Life-saving Humanitarian Assistance to Vulnerable Household Affected by Hurricane Dorian in the Bahamas</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In response to the dire humanitarian needs resulting from Hurricane Dorian, IOM is supporting the Government of Bahamas to provide life-saving assistance to the population affected by the hurricane. In particular, IOM is providing emergency shelter assistance and reconstruction tool kits for those households that can return to their partially destroyed homes. In addition, IOM is rolling out its Displacement Tracking Matrix (DTM) to identify, register and monitor displaced persons, including those in collective centres.</narrative>
  </description>
